Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.04,0:00:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to Dr. David Hawkins Sedona 2002\Nseries, The Way to God. Lecture 3, the
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.84,0:00:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,levels of consciousness, subjective and\Nsocial consequences.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.03,0:00:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Originally presented March 9th, 2002 at\Nthe Sedona Creative Life Center.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.92,0:00:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Today um the lecture was about uh the\Ntopic announced topic was about um
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.20,0:00:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget what it was\Nanyway we'll talk about it because
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.84,0:00:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,what I want to do we're we're giving a\Nseries of 12 lectures
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.23,0:00:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,uh so that I will then have said\Neverything I have to say
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.48,0:01:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that I can rest peacefully in the great\Nbeyond. You see, I don't want at the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.55,0:01:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,last moment to say, "Oh gosh, I forgot\Nto tell them all about it."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.92,0:01:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, that's a good rule of thumb, you\Nknow, for spiritual decisions
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.96,0:01:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is um what do you what do you want to be\Nresponsible for on your deathbed? And I
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.92,0:01:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,remember making a number of decisions in\Nmy life
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.43,0:01:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,u because uh the last moment is really\Nquite a confrontation.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.08,0:01:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, today uh the topics uh are\Nreally the emphasis of in other words in
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.75,0:01:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that talk we will try and cover that\Nsubject. However, we always call cover
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.88,0:01:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,all of it. So\Nevery lecture I want you know complete
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.96,0:01:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is is really complete in a way but the\Nemphasis is different.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.96,0:01:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we'll talk for a while and then uh\NI'll talk for a while and then we'll
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.15,0:02:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,have a break and then after that we'll\Nhave questions and answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.11,0:02:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,In the past, we've had people write them\Nand send them up. But, uh you can also
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.23,0:02:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,just because we have a very good um\Nsound system now, you can just ask them
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.12,0:02:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,from the audience, you raise your hand\Nand and uh I'll repeat the question. Uh
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.12,0:02:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that'll make it easier for everyone.\NAnd I don't see all that well to read
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.92,0:02:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,those cards anyway. I don't know what\Nthey say. I just
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.08,0:02:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,make a wild guess.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.95,0:02:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo, today we're emphasizing the um
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.00,0:02:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the map of consciousness as it applies.\Nuh what it is uh what is the world and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.12,0:02:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,um and then how that relates in general\Nto
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.12,0:03:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole field of consciousness.\NYou're aware that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.84,0:03:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness as defined in the writings\Nthat I've been doing can roughly be
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.72,0:03:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,defined as the linear and the nonlinear.\NThe linear being the ego, the world of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.08,0:03:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,form, definition, that which is\Ntemporal, that which the world believes
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.12,0:03:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,is reality.\NAs compared, and this is just a point of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.95,0:03:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,perception, it's not a different level,\Nbut compared to the nonlinear, which is
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.76,0:03:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,not definable as form,\Nis considered by a large percentage of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.72,0:03:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the world to be unreal.\Nuh and it's classically defined as
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.40,0:03:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual.\NThe map of consciousness crosses over
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.23,0:03:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,between the two. The importance of the\Nbook power versus force was after 30
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.48,0:04:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,years of not seeing anything about the\Nsubject at all. I suddenly became an
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.15,0:04:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,expert how to define how to make\Nmake it possible to go from the known to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.04,0:04:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the unknown.\NThe subjective
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.68,0:04:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the radical subjectivity of\Na spiritual state is difficult to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.32,0:04:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,describe and as I say for 30 years I\Nnever mentioned it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.91,0:04:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh and then saw this\Nmedical test called kinesiology. It was
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.56,0:04:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,considered a medical test. And when I\Nsaw John Diamond do that kinesiology,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.56,0:04:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,instantly I saw what what it was because\NI was myself already. My reality was
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.96,0:04:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,nonlinear and therefore I saw it from a\Ndifferent dimension than the rest of the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.44,0:04:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,audience.\NIt was always presumed to be a local
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.04,0:04:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,phenomena where a local condition causes\Na local reaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.75,0:05:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And I saw that it was a nonlinear\Nphenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.16,0:05:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and that the reaction was due to the\Npresence of a nonlinear state of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.88,0:05:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness.\NSo it opened then
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.24,0:05:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that kinesiology could be used beyond\Nthe linear
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.56,0:05:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and beyond the local. And in\Nexperimenting with it over many years
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.00,0:05:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,now, we found that we had a means of\Ndirectly accessing a field called
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.72,0:05:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness,\Nwhich is again um very iffy to people
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.68,0:05:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,who live in the\Nuh Newtonian paradigm of reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.91,0:05:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness in that definition is\Nwhether you're awake or asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.68,0:05:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness in the spiritual\Ndefinition of course is the field in the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.80,0:05:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,field from which one is aware of one's\Nexistence
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.75,0:06:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and the content of mind.\NIt is the field and it's not the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.68,0:06:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,content. So the world the ordinary world\Nlives in the world of content
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.84,0:06:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,takes the subjective uh for granted\Nwithout appreciating what it actually
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.08,0:06:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is.\NThe subjective is where
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.80,0:06:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,we exist. We exist. Our knowingness, our\Nawareness that we are or that anything
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.16,0:06:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,else is is only because of a radical\Nstate of subjectivity.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.56,0:06:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's roughly called awareness,\Nconsciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.03,0:06:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And the thing that differentiates it\Nfrom the Newtonian paradigm is that the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.91,0:06:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,subjective has no content.\NSo we might say that the world is let's
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.96,0:07:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,say if computers had arms and legs and\Nwe're walking around the computers in
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.63,0:07:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the ordinary world would all think that\Nthey're their software. They say I'm Mr.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.52,0:07:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,QuickBooks. Glad to meet you. And you're\NMiss
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.44,0:07:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss IRS computer form number 616. Glad\Nto meet you. And then there would be a
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.84,0:07:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,maverick in the midst of all of them who\Nwalks around and says, "Well, I'm my
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.84,0:07:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,hardware. I'm none of those things." And\Nthey would consider him slightly insane
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.63,0:07:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and put him off in a corner. So if he's\Nwise, he doesn't mention that and I
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.47,0:07:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,never did for 30 years.\Nthat I'm my hardware and the software
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.72,0:07:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,comes and goes. Uh and uh but the the\None reality behind all computers is
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.03,0:07:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,without hardware there's no software\Nprograms possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.31,0:07:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So the world thinks it's its programs.\NAll right. So today we're going to talk
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.72,0:07:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,about those programs and\Nof course illuminate the whole
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.28,0:08:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding of consciousness itself as\Na consequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.47,0:08:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Most everybody here has read power\Nversus force or maybe eye of the eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.36,0:08:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Either way, uh you know the map of\Nconsciousness has become extremely
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.16,0:08:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,wellnown. and it's widely quoted and I\Nget requests every day to reprint it in
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.44,0:08:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,some publication or article.\NSo it's become um a useful tool. So we
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.84,0:08:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,should really then understand what it\Nreally uh reflects. What does it really
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.63,0:08:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,reflect?\NAnd as we will see
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.44,0:08:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a way of it's a it's a way of\Ndescribing
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.68,0:08:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego is really what it is.\NIf we look at society we we were talking
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.04,0:08:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,about the map of consciousness as it\Nexpressed in today's society. If we look
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.12,0:08:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,at the world and society\Nuh what we see is the ego projected out
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.27,0:09:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,there.\NThe world itself is uh a playground,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.00,0:09:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,uh a graveyard, an amusement center,\Ndepending on your point of perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.32,0:09:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. So, uh I consider it\Nentertainment. It's sort of like turning
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.80,0:09:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,on the TV. And, uh yesterday morning's\Nnewspaper was was dramatic. It it had
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.16,0:09:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,two of the most horrible stories you\Ncould possibly read. And it just broke
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.64,0:09:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,me up because, you know, it's like the\Nworld pushes the extreme just like TV
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.00,0:09:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,programs do. Push the extreme.\NWhen was a baby that got left
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.12,0:09:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,three-year-old left home by its parents\Nwith the uh their pet python.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.60,0:09:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,When they came home, the baby was dead.\NThe python had strangled it to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.04,0:09:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What do they think the python was going\Nto do? Play dominoes with the kid? I
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.72,0:10:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,don't know. So anyway, you say, "Yeah,\Nright." Uhhuh. Well,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.88,0:10:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,when I was a kid, my grandmother would\Nalways read the newspaper and then she
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.39,0:10:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,would cry. She would always find a sad\Nstory and cry. And my grandfather would
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.20,0:10:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,get very irritated with her.\NMolly, when you cut that out, there's
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.56,0:10:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,this little three-year-old Tikeke. He\Nwas strangled to death by a python. And
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.27,0:10:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,she would weep and weep.\NSo to her, it was sad. Uh to me the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.44,0:10:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,story was like ridiculous. Like life is\Na theater of the absurd. Yeah, theater
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.27,0:10:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of the absurd. So we'll talk about these\Nlevels of consciousness to get them
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.64,0:10:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,clarified for once and for all what they\Nmean and clear up any confusions that
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.76,0:10:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,there could be about it. To begin with,\Nthey are neither better or worse. It is
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.12,0:10:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,not a hierarchy of worthiness\Nor accomplishment.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.00,0:11:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a way of looking like a prism. A\Nprism breaks up the light and to its
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.16,0:11:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,different colors. It doesn't mean that\Nultraviolet is better than blue or
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.12,0:11:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,better than green.\NSo what we've done here is break up you
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.92,0:11:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,know the level of levels of\Nconsciousness with a prism and these
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.07,0:11:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,would be the colors that come out. So\Nthese colors
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.72,0:11:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,these are what they are is progressive\Nlevels of power within the field of
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.27,0:11:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness. First of all\Num the higher you go the greater the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.07,0:11:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,power.\NIt's to some degree it's like a
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.07,0:11:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,thermometer\Nand this thermometer
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.24,0:11:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,then these are various degrees of power.\NThey are also various degrees of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.56,0:11:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They also are various\Ndegrees to which you might say the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.48,0:11:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,presence of God is consciously reflected\Ninto life.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.12,0:12:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,To transcend the opposite, it's\Nnecessary to give up a positionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.83,0:12:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And we use a thermometer as an example.\NYou can't just say put your finger here
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.80,0:12:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and say, "Well, above it it's hot and\Nbelow it's cold." And now hot and cold
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.24,0:12:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,are opposite. That's what the mind does.\NWe took that up in the lecture on or we
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.36,0:12:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,will be on transcending the opposites to\Nreach the state of so-called state of
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.88,0:12:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,enlightenment is necessary to drop all\Npositionalities
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.24,0:12:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in which duality disappears\Nand that is the pathway of adv advida
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.92,0:12:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,which we'll have a lecture on\Nany dropping of positionality. So
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.60,0:12:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,neither um the presence of God as it is\Nmanifested as it manifests and radiates
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.60,0:12:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,through a specific consciousness then\Num we would say at the top is
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.95,0:12:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that the light is clearer that there's\Nless uh darkness in the field and that's
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.68,0:13:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,why they're called enlightened states.\NThe light actually is almost an
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.39,0:13:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,experiential. It's almost like\Na great clarity and light does suffuse
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.07,0:13:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,everything.\NAs the ego imposes its uh
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.16,0:13:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,itself between truth and its own\Negoentricity, we might say that the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.51,0:13:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,bottom is uh egoentricity.\NLet's say that the bottom of the if the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.56,0:13:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,top is God, what is the bottom? The\Nbottom is
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.39,0:13:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,profound state states of egoentricity\Num
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.32,0:13:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which um considerable damage to\Nworld the world can come in our view of
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.12,0:13:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,it uh let's say Mr. been loud and\Ncalibrates at 70 which is down in here
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.16,0:13:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh\Nso that which is below brings tends to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.48,0:14:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,bring what the we consider somewhat\Ndestructive but that of course is a
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.88,0:14:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,point of view.\NIt was constructive from his viewpoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.76,0:14:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So again constructive and destructive\Nare only positionalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.44,0:14:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The levels of consciousness however we\Nwere able to calibrate using kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.36,0:14:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and I forget how we even started with it\Nbut um the levels are really
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.19,0:14:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,traditional. It's really the perennial\Nphilosophy only documented and I've been
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.27,0:14:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,having I was going to say brought up as\Na psychiatrist
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.44,0:14:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,brought up as a psychiatrist.\NI was brought up as a psychiatrist and
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.04,0:14:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,psychoanalyst and psych psychoanalyst\Nand uh so
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.12,0:14:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I naturally apply these things as I\Nunderstood life and the human mind. So
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.51,0:14:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,these are states that are both emotional\Nyou see emotional
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.07,0:15:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh intellectual and spiritual\Nand um these are the names by which we
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.51,0:15:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,commonly know these phenomena in daily\Nlife. anger, fear, grief, pride, hope,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.92,0:15:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,all those things. Then to give it uh\Nan additional usefulness,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.92,0:15:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it's been calibrated and the\Ncalibrations turned out to be
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.60,0:15:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,logarithms.\NSo that a move of a few points on the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.60,0:15:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,scale\Nuh as you're aware in a log is to tend
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.19,0:15:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to that that number. So it's a very\Nsizable move. Very sizable move.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.24,0:15:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The move from let's say 200 to 202\Ndoes not sound much in numerically but
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.63,0:15:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,because you're talking about the\Nlogarithm
