Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.27,0:29:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,dominating the consciousness field of\Nmankind. So what you could get away
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.55,0:30:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,with, what was acceptable in past uh\Ntimes, in past times it was assumed if
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.64,0:30:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,you captured an enemy naturally you\Nenslaved them, raped them, pillaged them
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.03,0:30:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and killed them often and mutilated them\Nin horrible ways. And that was
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.91,0:30:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,considered okay. It's the way the world\Nis and nobody questioned it. At a
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.79,0:30:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness level 207, there would be\Na cry of outrage, an outrage. Uh so
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.24,0:30:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the fact that our consciousness has now\Nemerged so a new emergence of awareness
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.20,0:30:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is dominating the whole field of human\Nconsciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.12,0:30:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,with profound implications for everyone.\NAll right. So 200 then denotes a
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.91,0:30:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,difference between\Nand again it is not a level of
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.96,0:30:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,opposites. It's not that 200 above is\None reality and below 200 is another
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.48,0:31:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,reality. It's not good versus bad. This\Nis a thermometer.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.24,0:31:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is the thermometer.\NAnd the presence of God, the presence of
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.91,0:31:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,love is what\Naccounts for the calibration.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.96,0:31:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Above this level, you go strong and\Nbelow it goes weak. And it looks like
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.24,0:31:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you're looking at true and false. It\Nlooks like you're looking at good and
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.52,0:31:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,evil. But that is not the case.\NThe case is that you see water. Water is
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.20,0:31:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,still water whether it's ice, liquid or\Nsteam.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.51,0:31:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing that changes there is\Ntemperature. Above this temperature you
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.27,0:31:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,got over 212 it changes its quality.\NThen below 212 it turns back into
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.79,0:31:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,liquid. it changes its quality, but it's\Nstill just water. Then at 32 degrees
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.84,0:31:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Fahrenheit, it changes its quality and\Nturns into a solid.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.88,0:32:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can't say steam is the opposite\Nof ice or that water is the opposite of
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.76,0:32:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,steam. You understand what I'm saying?\NI'm trying to get out of any trying to
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.79,0:32:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,use this in any kind of positionality.\NAs the temperature increases or
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.67,0:32:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,decreases\Nthen quality changes. The same with
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.12,0:32:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,light in a room. There is not two\Ndifferent things light and dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.08,0:32:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There is intense light. As the light\Ngets lower and lower and lower, it gets
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.91,0:32:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,dimmer and dimmer and dimmer. Then it's\Nharder and harder to see. And we say
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.08,0:32:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,it's dusk or dark. You know, there's\Nonly one variable and that's light. The
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.27,0:32:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,presence of light. That's the only\Nvariable. There's not two things, light
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.51,0:32:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and dark. You can't get a take take a\Nbox of darkness and put it someplace or
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.24,0:32:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,say shine me some darkness in this\Ncloset. It doesn't have any existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.39,0:32:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The only reality then is light and light\Nis either present or not present and
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.15,0:33:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,it's present to varying degrees. So the\Nanalogy is that the love of God is like
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.08,0:33:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the light and\Nup here the love of God is quite intense
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.51,0:33:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and down here it diminishes and uh\Nbecomes progressively darker.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.24,0:33:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,When this happens, the human emotion\Nthat goes with it
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.20,0:33:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,goes through the whole panorama\Nfrom an ecstatic state, a state of
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.76,0:33:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,state, there's a state beyond ecstasy, a\Nblissful state of absolute serenity and
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.88,0:33:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,stillness.\NAs the as the calibrated levels come
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.67,0:33:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,down, you see the shift of emotions. And\Nbelow 200 we notice that these emotions
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.00,0:33:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,are\Nclassically negative and painful.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.67,0:33:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And here down at the bottom they become\Nquite severe
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.91,0:34:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and suicide they even lead to suicide.\NThe interesting thing about calibrated
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.08,0:34:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,levels of consciousness\Nis that everybody has a calibrated level
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.27,0:34:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness the instant they're\Nborn. The instant they're born, there's
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.67,0:34:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,already a calibratable level of\Nconsciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.96,0:34:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,which has a certain implication. And\Nwe'll have another lecture with which we
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.52,0:34:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,talk just about karma itself.\NUh either life is extremely unfair
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.35,0:34:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,or there is a coherence and a spiritual\Nuh coherence to the universe in which
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.59,0:34:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,case there is no such thing as\Naccidental.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.24,0:34:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,In a coherent universe in which the\Npresence of God is the infinite context
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.04,0:34:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which all reality arises. Uh\Nthere is no such thing as an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.04,0:34:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Accident like the word chaos means a\Nlimitation of perception. It means from
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.32,0:34:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the Newtonian point of view it looks\Nlike an accident. But from the overall
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.80,0:35:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,point of view there are no accidents\Npossible. Then
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.96,0:35:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the infinite reality of God then is like\Nan infinite electromagnetic field.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.76,0:35:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Its power is absolute. Its power is\Nunlimited. Its power is infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.64,0:35:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,All that is is held within the infinite\Npower of the infinite context of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.24,0:35:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing can happen outside of it.\NConsequently, an accident is not
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.00,0:35:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,possible. For an accident to be so, it\Nwould have to be outside the infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.92,0:35:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,context of\Num the universe. And if it was there,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.88,0:35:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you wouldn't know it. So, no accident is\Npossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.11,0:35:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything falls within a coherence.\NEach thing is
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.35,0:35:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,where it is because of what it is.\NEach thing becomes the fulfillment of
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.92,0:36:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,its own essence and in so doing its\Ncharacteristics define where it will
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.76,0:36:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,position itself within the overall\Ninfinite field of power. So that you see
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.32,0:36:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing is causing anything.\NEverything is just being what it is. As
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.80,0:36:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,a consequence of it being what it is, it\Nautomatically moves in an infinite field
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.88,0:36:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,of power.\NIs that clear? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.83,0:36:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So that takes care of causality. Causal\Nand causality. It's important to
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.20,0:36:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,understand that because we want to get\Nit past the barriers of um picturing God
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.28,0:36:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,as some kind of a judgmental\Narbitrary
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.07,0:36:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,uh being. And people fear death because\Nnow you're going to meet the great
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.07,0:36:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,judgmentalism. Huh.\NAll right. So each thing is where it is
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.92,0:37:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's being what it is because out of\Nout of creation its essence then defines
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.92,0:37:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that if it has wings it flies. You see?\NYeah. But that's coming out of its own
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.52,0:37:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,essence. So those who seek God do so and\Nout of the evolution of their own
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.52,0:37:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness\Nbecause the quality of consciousness is
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.59,0:37:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to seek progressively seek to know its\Nits own nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.11,0:37:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\N>> Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.07,0:37:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Are questions permitted now or rather\N>> anytime. Anytime.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.32,0:37:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,>> In essence then are we saying if it's um\N>> if you you got to stand up and speak so
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.56,0:37:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I can hear.\N>> In essence you hear what he says. In
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.04,0:37:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,essence, are you saying that um if it's\Nnot there's no accidents then does that
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.28,0:37:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,make it predestined in a sense?\N>> That question always arises.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.32,0:38:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The entire universe is one karmic unity.\NPeople say you believe in karma. It's
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.96,0:38:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,not a matter of believing in karma.\NThe entire universe is one infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.48,0:38:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,coherence.\Nthe context of which has infinite power
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.68,0:38:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because a power arises out of context.\NTherefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.00,0:38:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the infinite potentiality that we\Ntend to call God arises the entire
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.28,0:38:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,universe as an obvious coherence.\NWhat was the question?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.80,0:38:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,>> There is an accident.\N>> Oh, accident. Yes. Right. So each thing
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.28,0:38:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,then what occurs is a result of the\Nessence of its own
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.20,0:38:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,uh reality.\NEach thing then you might say has its
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.96,0:38:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,own karma within the infinite coherence\Nof the universe. Nothing can fall
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.24,0:38:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,outside the universe. So consequently\Neverything within the universe is
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.72,0:39:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,subject to the laws of the universe.\NEach thing then
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.04,0:39:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is the result of what it is spiritually.\NWhat it is is the accumulated result of
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.72,0:39:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,its own decisions by its own spiritual\Nwill.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.44,0:39:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,By one's own spiritual will, one rises\Nor falls like a cork in the water. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.11,0:39:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Each moment we choose instant by instant\Nto constantly choose in one direction to
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.59,0:39:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,constantly choose the direction of the\Nlight light
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.76,0:39:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,uh eventuates and constantly going in\Nthis direction to refuse the light which
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.88,0:39:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is your privilege.\NYeah. Everyone is created free. One can
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.40,0:39:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,refuse God, refuse the love of God. One\Ncan condemn God. one can go
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.72,0:40:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,um and thereby choose the dark. The dark\Nis by one's own choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.76,0:40:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And those who ridicule God will then go\Nto realms occupied by those who ridicule
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.83,0:40:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,God.\NIf we calibrate them, they're not where
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.92,0:40:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,you want to go. And that's what Jesus\Nsaid. You don't want to go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.59,0:40:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He said it's not wrong. It's just that\Nyou really don't want to go where the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.28,0:40:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,sinful go when they die. Uh and the\NBuddha said the same at every great
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.28,0:40:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,religion and spiritual teacher tells you\Nthe same thing. You know that you really
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.44,0:40:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,don't want to go there. Uh anybody who's\Never been in profound guilt, shame,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.20,0:40:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,agony of depression and loss or terror\Nor hopeless rage. Uh those are just uh
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.35,0:40:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,those are the um approach approaches to\Nhell. And when you get to where really
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.56,0:41:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,gets bad. So the great teachers have\Nadvised us that it's not where you want
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.56,0:41:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to go. And that is that is a correct\Nstatement.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.24,0:41:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Um so it's not that we're pre\Npredestined
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.00,0:41:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,because predestination sounds arbitrary.\NUh
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.52,0:41:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you can only be that which you are. Let\Nme answer it that way. By the nature of
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.52,0:41:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,existence and beingness, one can only be\Nwhat one is.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.04,0:41:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What one is, one has sculpted by one's\Nown hand. So then there in lies the
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.64,0:41:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite justice of God.\NAll right? So the these emotions then as
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.59,0:41:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,they go up the scale become increasingly\Nagreeable.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.07,0:41:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,These are everybody comes to see the\Ndoctor in these states. This is my
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.16,0:42:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,office down here. Despair and anxiety\Nand depression and uh angriness and um
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.28,0:42:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,people don't see me out of uh arrogance\Nbut yeah they do. Uh
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.20,0:42:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,uh anyway as we go up uh as we go up we\Nsee the levels are far more uh and
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.00,0:42:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that's because the process is different\Nhere. Here you at the level of integrity
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.88,0:42:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you have the be real true beginning of\Nempowerment at 200
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.64,0:42:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,below that you get inflation the reason\NI don't like politically correct is
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.48,0:42:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,because it calibrates at 190 and and\Nthere's a grading holier than thou
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.64,0:42:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,superiority about it and it it's not\Nheld up
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.52,0:42:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,it its results don't verify it. So\Nthere's an ego inflation egotism here.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.83,0:42:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The over here at the lower levels the\Nego like uh shrinks you see but here
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.04,0:43:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,it's inflamed and pridefulness.\NUm
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.16,0:43:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,here we have the anger that anger gives\Npeople a temporary sense of power. It's
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.24,0:43:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,a false sense of power. It's the most\Ndifficult problem I have. I I'm chief of
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.04,0:43:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,staff at a resident big residential\Nplace
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.80,0:43:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,uh where we have 50 teenage girls and\Ntheir main problem is angryness other
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.28,0:43:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,than impulsivity and poor judgment and\Ngetting into all kinds of horrible
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.68,0:43:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,trouble. Uh but\Nuh on a day-to-day level they're getting
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.16,0:43:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,along with each other is constantly\Nimpaired with angriness. They're always
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.28,0:43:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,angry. They're like Johnny One note. No\Nmatter what happens, their only response
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.35,0:43:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is anger. You know what I mean? If it's\Ntoo cool in the room, they're angry
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.04,0:43:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,about that. If it's too warm, they're\Nangry about that. If I mention a certain
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.56,0:43:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,subject, they're angry about that. And\Nif I don't, they're angry because I
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.88,0:43:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't mention it. So, I mean, it's just\Na proness to angriness.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.96,0:43:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't have any power, the next\Nbest if you if you fail power, see,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.80,0:44:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,these are all levels of weakness. If you\Ndon't have any real power, then the next
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.48,0:44:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,thing to do is to inflate yourself. So\Nyou see the puffed up arrogance of
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.31,0:44:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Malachevich. You know, he when they take\Nhis picture, he's always got his head up
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.72,0:44:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,like this. And\Nthe UN and all the world, all the
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.20,0:44:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,countries of the world have no right to\Nquestion what I do. I mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.59,0:44:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that's Wow. And\Nall right. So
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.83,0:44:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,from 200 down are really levels of\Nweakness and 200 and over are levels of
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.31,0:44:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,power. If you have real power, you don't\Nneed all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.40,0:44:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like\Nit's like self-esteem.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.88,0:44:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If you lack self-esteem, then you feel\Nyou need self-esteem.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.88,0:44:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have self-esteem, you don't need\Nself-esteem and you're not even
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.24,0:44:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,interested in it. You know, people think\Nyou're fine, you're glad they're happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.24,0:44:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If they don't think you're fine, it's\Ntheir problem. You know, what people
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.72,0:45:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,think about you is sort of irrelevant\Nbecause you're autonomous. So, these
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.48,0:45:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,people are not autonomous. what people\Nthink about them makes a big very big
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.20,0:45:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,difference because they're levels of\Nweakness. Then uh these are
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.07,0:45:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,levels of force. Up here you have power.\NPower just stands there by itself. Power
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.48,0:45:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,influences everything within its domain\Nas a consequence of that which it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.92,0:45:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That which you are has a more profound\Neffect on everything than that which you
