Dialogue: 0,1:43:45.84,1:43:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that perpetrator never appears to be\Nguilty is because she deserved it. She
Dialogue: 0,1:43:51.28,1:43:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,made me do it.\NShe made me do it. What's there to feel
Dialogue: 0,1:43:56.08,1:44:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,guilty about? Huh? To not own. So that\Nperson calibrates them below 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:03.60,1:44:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The difficulty with getting the kids in\Nthe girls ranch to to improve is you
Dialogue: 0,1:44:08.71,1:44:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,can't get them to own that they're the\Nauthor of their own decisions.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:13.92,1:44:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So here the blame is put out there. It's\Nthe other guy's fault.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:20.15,1:44:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,All right? So you affirm then at 200 k\Nof courage.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:25.76,1:44:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,When you get up to 250 is is neutrality.\N250 is you've become re released from
Dialogue: 0,1:44:32.32,1:44:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,attachments. There's a method known as\Nreleasing which I think is a very
Dialogue: 0,1:44:36.15,1:44:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,excellent method. Uh letting go, wanting\Nto change things, control things, become
Dialogue: 0,1:44:42.15,1:44:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,detached from things. So you you stop\Ncontrolling everything and stop worrying
Dialogue: 0,1:44:46.56,1:44:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,with people.\NIf you are a good releaser, you
Dialogue: 0,1:44:50.56,1:44:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,certainly end up at least at 250, which\Nis neutral. And neutral is very
Dialogue: 0,1:44:56.32,1:45:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,comfortable.\Npeople uh at neutral here. If you don't
Dialogue: 0,1:45:00.63,1:45:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,get the job, you kill yourself or you\Nkill the other guy or you blame
Dialogue: 0,1:45:04.88,1:45:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself. You go into depression and\Nstop eating and take an overdose.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:09.52,1:45:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Up here\Nin neutral, it's okay if it goes that
Dialogue: 0,1:45:13.76,1:45:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,way and it's okay if it doesn't. You\Ndon't have you're not riding on what
Dialogue: 0,1:45:17.84,1:45:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,happens out there. You're not living on\Nthe projections of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:22.32,1:45:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You're neutral. If you get the job, it's\Nokay. And if you don't, there's a lot of
Dialogue: 0,1:45:25.36,1:45:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,other ones. Anybody tells me there's\Nunemployment doesn't know what they're
Dialogue: 0,1:45:29.11,1:45:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,talking about. I can open the\Nunemployment page, the employment pages,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:33.76,1:45:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,jobs wanted, you know, help wanted pages\Nof any newspaper in the United States
Dialogue: 0,1:45:37.76,1:45:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and find three or four pages of jobs. I\Ncan walk down any street in America. It
Dialogue: 0,1:45:42.32,1:45:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,says help wanted anywhere. Do it in\NSedona. Says help wanted on every single
Dialogue: 0,1:45:46.56,1:45:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,block.\NIt's not out there. Unemployment is not
Dialogue: 0,1:45:50.40,1:45:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,out there. Unemployment is in your head.\NRight after World War II, all the vets
Dialogue: 0,1:45:55.44,1:46:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,came back. We all got 5220. I only got\N5220, but I also had three jobs at the
Dialogue: 0,1:46:00.96,1:46:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,same time,\Nright? Survival.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:06.48,1:46:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So, the willingness then\Nneutral is okay. As we get up to
Dialogue: 0,1:46:12.08,1:46:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,willingness, we have a whole different\Ninspiration. We become God is inspiring.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:17.52,1:46:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Things look hopeful. People in\Nwillingness are fun to be with. People
Dialogue: 0,1:46:21.36,1:46:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in willingness are cheerful, optimistic,\Nthey help.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:25.84,1:46:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If one or two people are trying to lift\Na sofa, a person in willingness comes
Dialogue: 0,1:46:28.96,1:46:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,over and says, "Can I help?" They just\Nautomatically do that. They do that
Dialogue: 0,1:46:32.80,1:46:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,because of that's who they are. Cuz when\Nyou moving moving up to
Dialogue: 0,1:46:39.44,1:46:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,lovingness, then you're becoming an\Nasset on the planet. These people are a
Dialogue: 0,1:46:44.00,1:46:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,detriment on the planet. You know, they\Nmake cannon fodder. They use they're
Dialogue: 0,1:46:47.44,1:46:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,useful that way. Cannon fodder.\NBut they're not really an asset. In
Dialogue: 0,1:46:53.36,1:47:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,fact, the 78 below percent below\Nuh that level there are really supported
Dialogue: 0,1:47:00.56,1:47:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,by these at the top. These are the\Npeople at the top that allow to keep
Dialogue: 0,1:47:03.67,1:47:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,these people alive. If it wasn't for the\Npeople at the top, they wouldn't have
Dialogue: 0,1:47:07.28,1:47:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,sidewalks to walk on. You know what I\Nmean? You wouldn't have a car to get
Dialogue: 0,1:47:10.88,1:47:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,into.\NYou wouldn't have the steel to make the
Dialogue: 0,1:47:13.84,1:47:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,car. It's the people up here that\Nprovide the jobs, that provide the
Dialogue: 0,1:47:17.60,1:47:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,income, that provide the taxes, that\Nprovide the services of which these
Dialogue: 0,1:47:22.48,1:47:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,people live because they don't pay any\Nthese people don't pay any taxes.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:26.40,1:47:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So these people are powerfully\Nproductive. Powerfully productive. So
Dialogue: 0,1:47:31.11,1:47:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the sales manager just gets the team\Ntogether. He gives them a pep talk. They
Dialogue: 0,1:47:35.36,1:47:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,all feel fantastic when they walk out.\NIt's because he's probably at least
Dialogue: 0,1:47:39.60,1:47:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,around 350 or so. He's up there in the\Npositive. These are the go-getters of
Dialogue: 0,1:47:45.44,1:47:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the world. Go-Getters of the world. Then\Nwhat gives them their power is
Dialogue: 0,1:47:50.08,1:47:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,intention. Intention. So what Wernernner\Ntaught in s if it's your intention
Dialogue: 0,1:47:56.80,1:48:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,absolutely to get to that lecture at\N1:00 you will be there. And failure to
Dialogue: 0,1:48:02.71,1:48:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,be there 1:00 is a defect of intention.\NSo we're not always made you responsible
Dialogue: 0,1:48:07.19,1:48:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,for your intention. It means your\Nintention is out. Your integrity is out.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:12.32,1:48:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,If your intention is there, intention\Novercomes all kinds of obstacles. And a
Dialogue: 0,1:48:17.28,1:48:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,fierce determined intention can overcome\Nalmost anything in this world.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:22.71,1:48:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Fierce intention\Nis what you discover in sports when you
Dialogue: 0,1:48:28.40,1:48:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,reach or in exercise or in labor. When\Nyou reach the point beyond which you
Dialogue: 0,1:48:34.23,1:48:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot go,\Nyou white knuckle it, clench your teeth,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:39.92,1:48:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and by your intention, you drive through\Nthe barrier.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:44.56,1:48:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an incredible experience to do it.\NMany people have had it in sports,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:50.88,1:48:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,running, and various various ways. I\Ndiscovered it in a warehouse when I
Dialogue: 0,1:48:54.71,1:49:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,could not lift one more box of canned\Ngoods in Theville, Wisconsin.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:00.96,1:49:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,110° in a pee canery and 110° in this\Nwarehouse with no windows and I could
Dialogue: 0,1:49:06.71,1:49:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,not lift one more box. Not one more.\NAnd uh I was never a heavyweight to
Dialogue: 0,1:49:12.88,1:49:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,begin with. And anyway uh after maybe 12\Nor 14 hours in this heat, no water and
Dialogue: 0,1:49:19.76,1:49:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,no well I said I can't do it. And then\Nsomething came up and there was this
Dialogue: 0,1:49:25.11,1:49:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,incredible decision to go through the\Nbarrier and I crashed through the
Dialogue: 0,1:49:29.36,1:49:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,barrier and all of a sudden the boxes\Nbecame weightless. I lifted them like
Dialogue: 0,1:49:34.08,1:49:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,feathers. I could keep I could have kept\Ngoing for days and I've done that many
Dialogue: 0,1:49:37.60,1:49:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,times on lifting stone and all. Once you\Ndiscover what's beyond that barrier, the
Dialogue: 0,1:49:42.56,1:49:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the runner discovers that pushes itself\Nto the limit and will not accept the
Dialogue: 0,1:49:47.36,1:49:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,limit and by intention drives through\Nit. And suddenly the runningness half
Dialogue: 0,1:49:50.63,1:49:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,happens of its own. The runningness\Nhappens of its own
Dialogue: 0,1:49:55.67,1:50:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to some degree. This is also exactly the\Nsame as it is with spiritual work. When
Dialogue: 0,1:50:00.08,1:50:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you get to a certain point, you cannot\Ngo any further
Dialogue: 0,1:50:03.76,1:50:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and suddenly you're out in the free and\Neverything happens spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:09.04,1:50:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So willingness then\Nwillingness is also the open door to
Dialogue: 0,1:50:12.88,1:50:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,success. Willingness is powerful because\Nthe person here owns that it's their
Dialogue: 0,1:50:19.44,1:50:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,intention. Owns takes responsibility.\NThey're optimistic. They're willing.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:24.48,1:50:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,World is hopeful. And God now becomes an\Ninspiration. Inspiration.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:29.84,1:50:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,acceptance is even higher than that\Nbecause acceptance now
Dialogue: 0,1:50:34.71,1:50:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,uh there's a willingness to forgive\Nuh on a spiritual level uh acceptance is
Dialogue: 0,1:50:41.36,1:50:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,a harmonious and more merciful way when\Nwe were talking this morning instead of
Dialogue: 0,1:50:46.48,1:50:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,condemning your ego as as being the evil\Nin you and all the rest the devil and
Dialogue: 0,1:50:50.88,1:50:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Satan and giving it all kinds of hor\Nhorrific names
Dialogue: 0,1:50:54.63,1:51:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,if we're accepting then we accept it we\Nforgive the ego for being what it is I
Dialogue: 0,1:51:00.71,1:51:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,mean it grew up as an animal. What do\Nyou think it's going to do?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:05.11,1:51:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Algebra. You know the animal you got to\Ndo algebra.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:09.28,1:51:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So we transcend positionality\Nthrough forgiveness and acceptance. We
Dialogue: 0,1:51:16.15,1:51:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,come into a merciful\Nmerciful state of mind. If you're
Dialogue: 0,1:51:21.11,1:51:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,merciful towards your animal then then\Nyou're merciful towards other people's
Dialogue: 0,1:51:25.92,1:51:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,animal. Huh? So when somebody passes you\Non the highway, you say, "Good luck. I
Dialogue: 0,1:51:30.48,1:51:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,don't care if he gets in front of me."\NYou know what I mean? We're all going to
Dialogue: 0,1:51:32.48,1:51:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,arrive at the same place, same time\Nanyway, which is the next stop and go
Dialogue: 0,1:51:36.15,1:51:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,live. We're all going to be sitting\Nthere at the red. So let him get a car.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:39.44,1:51:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It makes a difference.
